          "Correct (1) vs Incorrect (0)",
          "9353 learners",
          "Algebra I and Bridge to Algebra",
          "Answer Sequences with Length of Answer",
          "[Sequences of Answers, Student Priors]",
          "BKT models only consider a finite set of parameters per knowledge component without considering learner-specific parameters.",
          "BKT with student parameters uses negative log likelihood as the objective function.\n\nIn essence, some of the BKT parameters are specific for each student.",
          "Authors extract student specific features that are used in the models: A priori knowledge of skill and learning rate of student which has impact on the probability of transitioning a state from unknown to known.",
          "BKT, BKT_L0, BKT_T, BKT_L0_T",
          "10-Fold Cross-Validation",
          "Algebra I\n{RMSE: 0.34060 - BKT_L0_T→ Skill model B, Accuracy: 0.85016 -  BKT_L0_T→ Skill model B}\n\nBridge to Algebra\n{RMSE: 0.35482 - BKT_L0_T→ Skill model B, Accuracy: 0.83389 -  BKT_L0_T→ Skill model B}",
          "The authors also have 2 skill models. \n\nAuthors find that adding student-specific probability of learning is more important than probability of initial mastery. ",
          "Only BKT is explored. \n\nLimityed number of datasets.\n\nDoes not consider student-specific versions of 2 parameters: pSlip or pGuess\n\n"
        ]
      ],
